 -- Matthias Klose <doko@ubuntu.com>  Thu, 31 Jul 2008 17:37:40 +0200

python2.4 (2.4.5-5) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Update to 20080731, taken from the 2.4 release branch, only change:
    - Fix issue #2620, CVE-2008-3142, overflow checking when allocating or
      reallocating memory was not always being done properly in some python
      types and extension modules.
  * CVE-2008-3143 was fixed in 2.4.5-1.
  * Fix issues #2588, #2589, CVE-2008-3144, fix potential integer underflow
    and overflow conditions in the PyOS_vsnprintf C API function.
  * Fix CVE-2008-2315, more overflow checking in extension modules.

 -- Matthias Klose <doko@debian.org>  Thu, 31 Jul 2008 07:28:47 +0200

