 -- Matthias Klose <doko@debian.org>  Thu, 30 Mar 2006 23:42:37 +0200

python2.4 (2.4.2+2.4.3c1-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix upgrade error (#359829).
  * Fix the _bsddb configury (#359830).

 -- Matthias Klose <doko@debian.org>  Wed, 29 Mar 2006 06:16:20 +0000

python2.4 (2.4.2+2.4.3c1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * SVN update up to 2006-03-25 (2.4.3 candidate 1).
    - Regenerate the documentation.
    - map.mmap(-1, size, ...) can return anonymous memory again on Unix.
      Ubuntu #26201.
    - pwd is now a builtin module, remove it from python-minimal.
  * Build-depend on libncursesw5-dev, ncursesw5 is preferred for linking.
    Provides UTF-8 compliant curses bindings.
  * Build-depend on libdb4.4-dev.
  * Fix difflib where certain patterns of differences were making difflib
    touch the recursion limit.
  * python2.4-tk: Suggest tix instead of tix8.1.
  * Move config/Makefile from the -dev package into the runtime package
    to be able to use the bdist_wininst distutils command. Closes: #348335.
  * python2.4-minimal: Cleanup byte-code files on removal. Closes: #351325.
  * Add a build conflict on python2.4-xml, else test_minidom fails.

 -- Matthias Klose <doko@debian.org>  Mon, 27 Mar 2006 18:28:22 +0000

python2.4 (2.4.2-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * SVN update up to 2006-01-11
    - pwd is now a builtin module, remove it from python-minimal.
  * Depend on python-central.
  * python2.4-tk: Suggest tix instead of tix8.1.
  * python2.4-minimal: Add user fields Python-Version and Python-Runtime.
  * Add a --debian option for the distutils install command to install
    into /usr/lib/pythonX.Y/dist-packages.

